Khalik Allah: Street Opera @ Heron Arts
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Please join us for the opening reception of Street Opera, an exhibition of still photography from Khalik Allah, at Heron Arts from 6-9pm! Khalik Allah's Street Opera is a vivid and visceral portrayal of urban life and the human characters that inhabit it. Shooting at 125th and Lexington in Harlem, Allah's street photography gives a powerful glimpse into the spirit and character of those living in poverty. The evening will also feature performance by live jazz quartet Acme Anvil Drop. Heron Arts is pleased to present this work in association with Yerba Buena Center for the Arts, as an opening reception for their afternoon screening of Allah's film work Field Niggas. View Field Niggas at Yerba Buena Center for the Arts Saturday August 15th, 4-6pm. Notable press: The New York Times - http://nyti.ms/1Eqw8nt TIME - http://ti.me/1MYD3au
Saturday, August 15, 2015, 6 PM - 9 PM in PDT

Community Supported PLACEmaking
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
A night of dialogue and dining, music and movement. PLACE (aplaceforsustainableliving.org) and Community Supported Everything are co-creating a night of shared Dialogue and Dining, Music and Movement. You can participate in the following ways: 1) Pledge to donate for a dinner dish. Participate in intimate conversation about Community Supported PLACEmaking in Portland and in the Bay. 2) Bring a conversation topic or project idea to the couch conversation. 3) Prepare yourself for exquisite shamanic contact dancing onstage. Rules-- ONE dance on stage at a time... even if it's a half-dozen swirly bodies. Post in comments if you're up to get down. $ 5-20 suggested donation for 6-7 dinner spot (limited to 10 guests). $ 5-15 suggested donation for 7-10 performance and play. Schedule: 6:00 - 7:00 -- Meal Prepared with PLACE and CSE core members. 7:00 - 10:00 -- music and dialogue on the couch, dancing on the stage. MUSIC: Lorka Scher of titlewillcome Flow Flower Jeff of New Noetic MOVEMENT: Flow flower Calypso Oolala Mylo Gan DIALOGUE: Jeff of PLACE. Sam Smith of CSE. Mylo of Gatter.io DINING: Vegan & Gluten-Free! Call Mylo at (503)819-1772 to reserve your spot. About Community Supported Everything (Portland, OR) "CSE Lab is a community project incubator operating primarily in a cooperative exchange and the gift economy. http://communitysupportedeverything.org/ Description "We create a fun, interactive space for people to come together, share their passions, skills, dreams, and find support from their community. "We map our collective resources so we can make connections and help get ideas off the ground. We build relationships and a network of support- a place where asking for help is not just OK, but essential. This is a place to bring your dreams, your crazy ideas, your on-hold projects- the things you cannot do alone. We're here for you! "Inspired by Community Supported Agriculture where supportive relationships are forged directly between the community and local farmers, Community Supported Everything encourages and enables mutually beneficial relationships within our communities. We create spaces for neighbors to share their ideas, find support and offer their talents to incubate projects that benefit the community as a whole."

Groupmuse at Monument: Blithe Ignorance of the Future Cataclysm
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Come lie on carpets and pillows and enjoy an evening of curious and beautiful string quartets. This is the first Groupmuse of Monument, a large and creative community space in San Francisco. Bring your loved ones, and please RSVP at https://www.groupmuse.com/events/3318 so we can calculate the correct carpet radius :-) This event is 21+ only. Program: Terry Riley, "Sunrise of the Planetary Dream Collector" Shostakovich Quartet No. 3 Beethoven Quartet No. 1 7:30pm doors 8pm music begins! Groupmuse asks for a $10 suggested donation for the musicians. Some stories: ......... #1 It's 1946. Dmitriy Shostakovich has just had his Symphony no. 9 censured by Soviet authorities. He has written a new string quartet, the haunting and challenging No. 3. For its premiere, most likely so that he would not be accused of "formalism" or "elitism," Shostakovich renames the movements in the manner of a war story: Blithe ignorance of the future cataclysm Rumblings of unrest and anticipation Forces of war unleashed In memory of the dead The eternal question: Why? And for what? ......... #2 It's 1980. In twenty years, NASA will commission you to take sounds of space and weave them into music. This sounds will come from plasma wave receivers flown on a variety of Milky Way spacecraft over a period of 40 years. That is yet to come: for now, you are writing Sunrise of the Planetary Dream Collector. It is an improvisational piece, inspired by a whimsical idea: each day, a dream collector collects the dreams of all the planet's sleepers, and redistributes them again next day. You write the composition for the Kronos Quartet, your new collaborators. It is in Dorian mode, in fourteen-beat modules (because seven!). They players choose the modules they are inspired to play. To read more about the amazing movement that is Groupmuse: https://www.groupmuse.com/about

Lips & Rhythm 40 with Dan Sherman
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Dan Sherman is a homie of ours who has cut his teeth DJing and throwing parties on the scene in San Francisco for some cosmic time. If you've ever seen him spin at Qoöl then you know what we're talking about yo. This guys got the chops and we are set to cut him loose for a two hour take-over on Lips & Rhythm this weekend. Ya'll best keep it locked for an adventure into some healthy house with this badman DJ and budding producer. TUNE IN! 8-10pm (PST) please download the TuneIn App for a good quality stream http://tunein.com/radio/Radio-Valencia-s139700/ Or use: www.Radiovalencia.fm ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// Dan Sherman: Dan Sherman lives with his cats, the godfather of his cats and a cool Swiss chick in San Francisco. He is originally from Wisconsin, the home of Leinenkugel beer, which is unfortunately not sold in San Francisco. In addition to being a human, a friend to many and possibly a foe to a few, Dan is also DJ and a producer. He is a resident DJ for Qoöl. He is also a resident DJ for Concept, an event series he helps run with good pals Will Spencer and Alex Blackstock , and a co-founder of Sui Generis, an event series that brings electronic music artists who’ve never been to San Francisco, to San Francisco. Dan has released a few remixes on Loöq Records and is planning to release his first EP of original productions on the same label towards the end of 2014.
Saturday, August 2, 2014, 8 PM - 10 PM in PDT
Radio Valencia
